                {
                    "title": "&nbsp;",
                    "content": "<div class=\"footnotes\">\n<h5>Footnotes</h5>\n\n<ol>\n\t<li><a href=\"https://openknowledge.worldbank.org/bitstream/handle/10986/32639/9781464815324.pdf\" target=\"_blank\">The World Bank, Women, Business and the Law, table 1.1, Washington, D.C., 2020 (last accessed on 13 April 2020) </a>. (<a data-storymaps=\"MJ-ACTION-1615162873125\" data-storymaps-type=\"navigate\">\u21e1 back to text</a>)</li>\n\t<li><a href=\"https://www.ilo.org/dyn/normlex/en/f?p=NORMLEXPUB:12100:0::NO:12100:P12100_INSTRUMENT_ID:312245:NO\" target=\"_blank\">ILO Convention No. 100, article 2 (accessed on 13 April 2020) </a>. (<a data-storymaps=\"MJ-ACTION-1615162904905\" data-storymaps-type=\"navigate\">\u21e1 back to text</a>)</li>\n\t<li><a href=\"https://www.ilo.org/dyn/normlex/en/f?p=NORMLEXPUB:12100:0::NO::P12100_INSTRUMENT_ID:312256\" target=\"_blank\">ILO Convention No. 111, article 2 (accessed on 13 April 2020) </a>. (<a data-storymaps=\"MJ-ACTION-1615162986381\" data-storymaps-type=\"navigate\">\u21e1 back to text</a>)</li>\n\t<li><a href=\"https://unstats.un.org/unsd/methodology/m49/\" target=\"_blank\">For statistical purposes, Tuvalu is categorized as both a least developed country and a small island developing State </a>. (<a data-storymaps=\"MJ-ACTION-1615163160760\" data-storymaps-type=\"navigate\">\u21e1 back to text</a>)</li>\n\t<li><a href=\"https://openknowledge.worldbank.org/bitstream/handle/10986/32639/9781464815324.pdf\" target=\"_blank\">The World Bank, Women, Business and the Law, table 1.1, Washington, D.C., 2020 (last accessed on 13 April 2020) </a>. (<a data-storymaps=\"MJ-ACTION-1615163202040\" data-storymaps-type=\"navigate\">\u21e1 back to text</a>)</li>\n\t<li><a href=\"https://www.ilo.org/dyn/normlex/en/f?p=1000:12100:0::NO::P12100_INSTRUMENT_ID,P12100_LANG_CODE:312245,es:NO\" target=\"_blank\">International Labour Organization (ILO) Equal Remuneration Convention, 1951 (ILO Convention No. 100) </a>. (<a data-storymaps=\"MJ-ACTION-1615163265254\" data-storymaps-type=\"navigate\">\u21e1 back to text</a>)</li>\n\t<li><a href=\"https://www.ilo.org/dyn/normlex/en/f?p=NORMLEXPUB:12100:0::NO::P12100_INSTRUMENT_ID:312256\" target=\"_blank\">ILO Discrimination (Employment and Occupation) Convention, 1958 (ILO Convention No. 111)</a>. (<a data-storymaps=\"MJ-ACTION-1615163271643\" data-storymaps-type=\"navigate\">\u21e1 back to text</a>)</li>\n\t<li><a href=\"https://unstats.un.org/sdgs/report/2019/regional-groups/\" target=\"_blank\">Countries and territories have been organized in regional groupings under the Sustainable Development Goals (SDGs) indicator framework </a>. (<a data-storymaps=\"MJ-ACTION-1615163278053\" data-storymaps-type=\"navigate\">\u21e1 back to text</a>)</li>\n\t<li><a href=\"https://www.ilo.org/dyn/normlex/en/f?p=NORMLEXPUB:11001:0::NO:::\" target=\"_blank\">ILO, Information System on International Labour Standards (NORMLEX), Ratifications by country </a>. (<a data-storymaps=\"MJ-ACTION-1615163283408\" data-storymaps-type=\"navigate\">\u21e1 back to text</a>)</li>\n</ol>\n</div>\n",
